-- Pacers Beat Magic in Overtime to Take 3-1 Lead in NBA Playoffs
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-05T21:14:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-05/pacers-beat-magic-in-overtime-to-take-3-1-lead-in-nba-playoffs.html
The Indiana Pacers beat the Orlando
Magic 101-99 in overtime to take a 3-1 lead in their National
Basketball Association first-round playoff series.  David West  had 26 points and 12 rebounds to lead Indiana.
Jason Richardson scored 25 points and Glen Davis had 24 for the
Magic, which wiped out a 12-point fourth quarter deficit to
force overtime.  Indiana can clinch the best-of-seven series with a home win
in Game 5 in three days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  